<p>Sometimes it&rsquo;s annoying to get those warnings while you work on the layout stuff.</p>
<p>Based on <a href="https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/debugging.html#warnings">RN documentation</a> you can turn them off by setting:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#a6e22e">console</span>.<span style="color:#a6e22e">disableYellowBox</span> <span style="color:#f92672">=</span> <span style="color:#66d9ef">true</span>;
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>You can put it inside your App.js file. I don&rsquo;t suggest you to commit this but as temporary string is definitely acceptable.</p>